{
  "texts": [
    "The PI1M dataset lacks information regarding the ionic conductivity of the polymers.",
    "As such, we utilize the minGPT model for unconditional generation during the pretraining phase.",
    "Then, the pretrained minGPT model is fine-tuned to generate polymers with high conductivity, as previously described.",
    "Since the GNN model is trained on polymer data from the HTP-MD database, which primarily contains PEO-like polymers, it is not directly applicable for predicting the ionic conductivity of the more diverse polymers found in the PI1M dataset.",
    "As a result, we need generative models like GPT-based and diffusion-based models to produce new polymers that adhere to the same distribution as the HTP-MD dataset, allowing their conductivity to be accurately predicted by the GNN model."
  ]
}